title: By the King, a proclamation
author: England and Wales. Sovereign (1694-1702 : William III)
publisher: Printed by Charles Bill, and the executrix of Thomas Newcomb ...,
notes: Reproduction of original in the Guildhall, London.
"Given at our court at Kensington the three and twentieth day of January, 1697, in the ninth year of our reign."
Pertains to: An Act against corresponding with the late King James and his adherents.
